Create Measures, Hierarchies and Groups 10

Step 1. Create Measures


Steps

  1. To create measures click on New Measure button from the home page of PowerBI Desktop.
  2. Enter the DAX formula in the formula bar and press Enter

Follow the same steps to create the following measures.

.Total Shooting = COUNT('Mass Shootings'[ShootingID])


.Total Victims = SUM('Mass Shootings'[TotalVictims])


.Victims Per Shooting = DIVIDE([.Total Victims], [.Total Shooting])


.YOY VPS % =
VAR PYVPS =
CALCULATE([.Victims Per Shooting], DATEADD('Calendar'[Date],-1, YEAR))
RETURN
DIVIDE(([.Victims Per Shooting] - PYVPS), PYVPS)


.Average YOY = AVERAGEX(VALUES('Calendar'[Year]), [.YOY VPS %])



Step 2. Create Date and Geography Hierarchy

To create date hierarchy,  right click on the Year field and select New Hierarchy.  Rename the Hierarchy as Date Hierarchy.

Drag and drop Month and Days of Week fields to the Date Hierarchy.

                               


Follow the same steps to create Geography Hierarchy for State and City


Step 3. Create Age Group for Shooters' Age




Steps

  1. To create groups Right Click on Age of Shooter field and select New Group.
  2. In the Groups dialogue box provide the name of the group
  3. Press and hold control key on your keyboard and select the ages to be grouped. in this case we will create Age Groups -20, 21-30, 31-40, 41-50, 51-60, 60+. We will create one group at a time.
  4. Once you select the ages to be included press Group button.
  5. Rename groups with the new group name such as 21-30 etc.
  6. After creating all groups check the Include Other Groups button to include values that are not grouped
  7. The final step is to click Ok button.


This youtube video provides explanation on implicit and explicit measures and how to create measures for our reporting.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A95nqPLdmRU
